reacs.QuantHlp: Differential c/s with respect to angle

x4freetext: Data presented on fig.1 (a).
Angular dependencies of differential cross
section were measured in an independent experiment
using a detector arranged outside the scattering
chamber with an angular resolution of (+ -1) degr.
The error in the absolute values of the
cross sections was about 10% and was determined
primarily by the errors in estimating target thickness
and in calibrating the current integrator. The
uncertainty in target thickness was 5%.
Statistical error

x4freetext: No explanation of relative units is given.
Data presented on fig. 2.
ANG-AZ-RL is an azimuthal angle between reaction planes
ANG-RSL - ANG1 resolution.
a polar angle between beam and proton.
a polar angle between beam and gamma-quantum.
Protons were recorded by four surface barrier
silicon detectors with the thickness of sensitive
region up to 350 mu-m. The angular resolution of the
detectors was (+ -2) degr.
Gamma-quanta were detected by four
scintillation detectors with NaI(TI) crystals
arranged at a fixed angular spacing of 32.5 degr. on
a moving horizontal ring platform outside the
scattering chamber.
